message: Hey future player! The 'growth serum' is your best friend initially: use it once on each large or medium base ingredient to get 'grown' items with increased value. The first use on a 'grown' hybrid (like an amphibious creature) can also boost its value to 'super-grown'. However, NEVER use the growth serum a second time on a hybrid, as it will make its value negative ('ultra-grown'). The 'mutation catalyst' usually makes items worthless (value 0), so avoid it unless you discover a specific positive 'mutant' combination. The highest scores come from combining 'grown' animals from different environments (land+water for amphibious) and then giving that hybrid one more boost with the growth serum. Focus on one main high-value item and submit when further actions seem risky!

The Mutation Catalyst is generally risky, often dropping values to zero or negative. However, its most valuable effect is on items that are *already mutant and have a negative or zero value*; applying the catalyst again to these can transform them into high-scoring 'super-mutants' (I saw up to 60 points). Aim to get an item to 'super-grown' via serum, then if it dips to zero or negative, try the catalyst on it for a potential breakthrough. Remember your score won't drop below zero, so you can risk experiments on low/negative value items.
